summary.conclusion:
CONCLUSION: MT-6 optimized parameters do NOT generalize to challenging conditions.
  • 50.4x chattering degradation (highly significant, p<0.001)
  • 90% failure rate in MT-7 (vs 0% in MT-6)
  • Very large effect size (Cohen's d = -26.5)
  • RECOMMENDATION: Expand optimization to include challenging initial conditions

comparison.interpretation: MT-7 challenging conditions show 50.4x worse performance in chattering_index compared to MT-6 baseline (very large effect, highly significant (p<0.001))

metadata.null_hypothesis: MT-6 parameters generalize to MT-7 conditions (μ_MT6 = μ_MT7)
metadata.alternative_hypothesis: MT-6 parameters do NOT generalize (μ_MT6 ≠ μ_MT7)
